  "prompt": "How do you convert gallons to ounces?",
  "response": "To convert gallons to ounces, you need to understand the conversion factor between these two units of volume. There are 128 fluid ounces in one gallon. Therefore, to convert gallons to ounces, you multiply the number of gallons by 128.\n\nHere is the formula:\n\n\\[ \\text{ounces} = \\text{gallons} \\times 128 \\]\n\nFor example, if you have 3 gallons and you want to convert it to ounces:\n\n\\[ 3 \\, \\text{gallons} \\times 128 \\, \\text{ounces/gallon} = 384 \\, \\text{ounces} \\]\n\nSo, 3 gallons is equal to 384 ounces.",
